mxTextCell.title: Text
mxTextCell.label:
Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice
- Sekiro fights regular enemies, and from time to time, bosses
- Boss fights are much harder and have a much higher probability of killing the player
- Sekiro earns xp whenever he kills an enemy, and a lot of xp when killing a boss
- If Sekiro dies, he loses half of his xp. Upon reaching a new level the required xp is spent to level up
- When Sekiro dies, there is a 30% chance he will receive "Unseen Aid", allowing him to retain his current xp
- On the upgrade tree some skills can only be attained until obtaining prerequisite skills
- Skills have a different cost, ranging from 1 point to 5 points
